## Enumerations

### anonymous enum  {#a298addd8bf1eaddaaebcec3640429188}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="anonymous enum ">
The epoch that defines the auto-upgrade compatibility for the bitcode.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="a298addd8bf1eaddaaebcec3640429188a7f66f39da99244fad39ebe115c4053a0" />
<EnumerationListItem name="BITCODE_CURRENT_EPOCH">
 (= 0)
</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

LLVM guarantees in a major release that a minor release can read bitcode generated by previous minor releases. We translate this by making the reader accepting only bitcode with the same epoch, except for the X.0 release which also accepts N-1.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/bitcode/llvmbitcodes-h/#l00081">81</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/bitcode/llvmbitcodes-h">LLVMBitCodes.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
